{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FCurAVbECEp6Dr26jgizHh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Ai1nTajqSDN4nP3EWvSEVf","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Performance review for mobile","subagent_type":"code-review-expert","prompt":"Review performance implications of the changes in lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts. This code runs on a mobile device (React Native / Expo) — total title extraction must complete under 10 seconds.\n\nKey changes to assess:\n\n1. **`applyBlindOcrRepairToken`** (line ~878): Now runs 12 regex replacements per token (up from 4). Each uses lookbehind/lookahead with Unicode character classes like `[a-zà-ż]` and `[A-ZÀ-Ż]`. These are called per-word in `applyBlindOcrRepairMixedCase`.\n\n2. **`generateBlindOcrVariants`** (line ~958): Generates up to 2 variants (i-variant + l-variant) per candidate in the first 5 positions. Each variant runs through the full OCR repair pipeline.\n\n3. **`hasErraticCasing`** (line ~930): Called multiple times — in `buildCandidates` for early-position candidates AND in `normalizeOcrTitle`. Splits text on whitespace, then runs 2 regex matches per word.\n\n4. **`isLikelyGarbled`** multi-word check (line ~340): New `.some()` loop over words with regex test per word. Called for every candidate.\n\n5. **`passesHardFilters`** OCR normalization (line ~407): Creates `ocrNormForInstruction` via 2 regex replacements, then potentially calls `looksLikeCookingInstruction` twice (once on original, once on normalized).\n\n6. **The `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` regex** (line ~362): Now has ~50 alternations. Called for every candidate.\n\n7. **`buildCandidates`** (line ~678): Now applies `stripTrailingPageRef` (an additional regex) to every candidate line.\n\nConsider:\n- How many candidates typically exist? (up to 25 after prioritization)\n- How many lines in a typical OCR document? (50-200)\n- Regex with Unicode lookbehinds — are they expensive on Hermes/JSC?\n- Are there any O(n²) or worse patterns?\n- Could any of these regex create catastrophic backtracking?\n\nRead the file at /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts to assess the actual code."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8366,"cache_read_input_tokens":47620,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8366},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f3952b68-8982-4bda-aefc-f210110437d7","uuid":"6a6db66d-3cc5-475b-aa5b-bda7094c402c"}
